This paper investigates the numerical reasoning capabilities of NLP models, specifically question answering models, and probes token embedding methods on synthetic numerical tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves numerical tasks, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision), but these are less likely as the focus is primarily on NLP models.
